Node.js Express APIThis is a robust backend service built with Express 5.x, featuring built-in security middleware, compression, and rate limiting.🚀 Getting StartedFollow these steps to get your development environment running.1. PrerequisitesEnsure you have Node.js installed (v18 or higher recommended).2. InstallationClone the repository and install the dependencies:Bashnpm install
Note: download this please after installing3. Environment SetupCreate a .env file in the root directory to manage your environment variables (supported by dotenv):PlaintextPORT=3000
NODE_ENV=development
4. Running the AppDevelopment (with hot-reload):Bashnpm run dev
Production:Bashnpm start
🛠 Features IncludedPackagePurposeExpress 5.2The latest web framework for Node.js.HelmetSecures Express apps by setting various HTTP headers.Express Rate LimitBasic rate-limiting middleware to prevent Brute-force/DDoS.CompressionDecreases the size of the response body to increase speed.CORSConfigures Cross-Origin Resource Sharing.🧹 Code QualityWe use ESLint and Prettier to maintain high code standards.Linting: npm run lintFormatting: npm run format

/backend
├── src/
│   ├── config/          # Database connection &    environment variables
│   ├── controllers/     # Logic for handling requests/responses
│   ├── middlewares/     # Auth, Rate limiting (you have the dependency), Error handling
│   ├── models/          # Database schemas (PostgreSQL or MongoDB)
│   ├── routes/          # Definition of API endpoints
│   ├── services/        # Complex business logic (e.g., Project stats)
│   ├── utils/           # Reusable helper functions
│   └── app.js           # Entry point
├── .env                 # Sensitive info (DB_URL, JWT_SECRET)
├── .eslintrc.json       # Config for ESLint
├── .prettierrc          # Config for Prettier
└── package.json